description: {"blocks":[{"key":"6gmd6","text":"This protocol describes how to reversibly bond layers of poly(methyl methacrylate) (PMMA) and polydimethylsiloxane (PDMS) using thermo-compresison bonding. Usually, two layers of PMMA are sandwiched around a center layer of PDMS. While compressed, all materials are heated to the softening temperature of the PMMA. They are then allowed to slowly cool to room temperature before removing from compression. The result should produce a bubble-free lamination between both PMMA-PDMS interfaces without melting the PMMA or significantly distorting micro-scale features. The times and temperatures in the SOP may be adjusted to accommodate different thicknesses or types of materials where a similar lamination-effect is desired.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"bold","offset":84,"length":4},{"style":"bold","offset":116,"length":4}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
guidelines: {"blocks":[{"key":"eob53","text":"To ensure success:","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"1mh2s","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"e6tbp","text":"The PMMA layers should be thicker than the middle PDMS layer (or at least substantially thicker than the thickest air pocket between the layers)","type":"ordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"91uj0","text":"The thicker material (PMMA in this case) must have a lower softening temperature","type":"ordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"f4upn","text":"The PMMA must be allowed to heat uniformly (see note)","type":"ordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"7h0bq","text":"The device must remain compressed until it is cooled completely (see note)","type":"ordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"k0i8","text":"Uniform pressure should be applied to both sides of the device","type":"ordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"8ojsc","text":"Holes and pockets in the PMMA should be greater than 100 um","type":"ordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"322f3","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"4cbsu","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"3k0nk","text":"Note: Minimum hold times for heating and cooling will vary depending on the type of oven used. For a standard lab without forced air circulation, use 2 hours for 3mm of material thickness, and add 1 hour per additional mm. See the attached guidelines from plexiglass for more information.   ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[{"key":0,"offset":289,"length":1}],"data":{}},{"key":"ce3ik","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{"0":{"type":"file","mutability":"","data":{"forceSelection":true,"guid":"8E5CC570F16B11E99344F7EAD31903D2","id":49510,"nestedSelector":null,"original_name":"Fabrication-Guidlines-Plexiglas-Annealing.pdf","placeholder":"/img/extensions/pdf.png","source":"https://s3.amazonaws.com/protocols-files/private/fe35c1f9aab2858711a6b522ffa60889b391cdbdcae3e871d68c66e067b4fc05/bsmg9ake.pdf"}}}}

steps.step: {"blocks":[{"key":"ejico","text":"Rinse all parts to be assembled under a stream of DI water to remove charred material or debris from machining.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"rjoh","text":"Sonicate the bags for 20 minutes","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"dge5l","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"bm2iu","text":" ","type":"atomic","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[{"key":0,"offset":0,"length":1}],"data":{}},{"key":"716t7","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{"0":{"type":"equipment","mutability":"","data":{"id":894,"brand":"Branson","can_edit":0,"guid":"7E8A3A10F17011E99344F7EAD31903D2","link":null,"name":"Sonicator","sku":"B2510","specifications":"","type":"","vendor":{"id":0,"name":"","link":"","image":{"source":"","placeholder":""}},"file":null,"image":null}}}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"oph4","text":"Remove the parts from each bag, rinse thoroughly with DI water, and dry with compressed nitrogen. {"blocks":[{"key":"9mv6m","text":"Orient the chip so the features face up and inspect the surface of the device to ensure it is free from dust and debris. Scotch magic tape seems to work best, but it can also leave residue if it is firmly pressed onto the surface of the device. For best results, roll the tape back onto itself to form a \"wheel\" and lightly blot the PMMA.","type":"unstyled"}],"entityMap":{}}},"2":{"type":"equipment","mutability":"","data":{"id":897,"brand":"Olympus","can_edit":0,"guid":"67004EF0F17211E99344F7EAD31903D2","link":null,"name":"Stereoscopic Microscope","sku":"SZ40","specifications":"","type":"Microscope","vendor":{"id":0,"name":"","link":"","image":{"source":"","placeholder":""}},"file":null,"image":null}}}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"idd9","text":"Orient the PDMS membrane over the prepared PMMA layer, and peel away the PET layer protecting the side that contacts the PMMA.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"1rje1","text":"Clean the exposed PDMS with  MagicTape","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"bch4e","text":" ","type":"atomic","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[{"key":0,"offset":0,"length":1}],"data":{}},{"key":"972a1","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{"0":{"type":"notes","mutability":"","data":{"blocks":[{"data":{},"depth":0,"entityRanges":[],"inlineStyleRanges":[],"key":"4j8uk","text":"The MagicTape will not leave residue on PDMS as easily as with PMMA. Press into the PDMS and clean thoroughly, as PDMS is a dust magnet.","type":"unstyled"}],"entityMap":{}}}}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"18k8n","text":"Using the tapered dowel pins, lower the PDMS onto the PMMA chip. When the material get close, press in the middle of the PDMS to start the adhesion process, then allow the materials to adhere from the middle outwards. ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"9d0ru","text":"Remove one of the taper pins and crease the PDMS/PET at that corner. Peel off the top layer of PET.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"3jhjq","text":" ","type":"atomic","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[{"key":0,"offset":0,"length":1}],"data":{}},{"key":"5prrn","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"flo34","text":" ","type":"atomic","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[{"key":1,"offset":0,"length":1}],"data":{}},{"key":"ei98s","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{"0":{"type":"notes","mutability":"","data":{"blocks":[{"data":{},"depth":0,"entityRanges":[],"inlineStyleRanges":[],"key":"a618","text":"It helps to peel the PET parallel to the device to create a large difference in the circumference of the PET/PDMS as the materials bend. This facilitates an easier release of the PET from the PDMS.","type":"unstyled"}],"entityMap":{}}},"1":{"type":"notes","mutability":"","data":{"blocks":[{"data":{},"depth":0,"entityRanges":[],"inlineStyleRanges":[],"key":"8pr83","text":"If the PDMS wrinkles, distorts, or comes of the PMMA while peeling the second PET layer, use the tapered dowel pins to lower the PDMS onto the PMMA again and realign features as necessary.","type":"unstyled"}],"entityMap":{}}}}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"eo2h9","text":"If any bubbles remain under the PDMS, inspect for dust. Bubbles may be a result of the PDMS wrinkling over the PMMA or a spot of dust. Where there is dust, peel back the PDMS and blot with MagicTape to remove.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"5vrhv","text":"Clean the exposed PDMS with MagicTape","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"ai2k8","text":" ","type":"atomic","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[{"key":0,"offset":0,"length":1}],"data":{}},{"key":"868vj","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{"0":{"type":"notes","mutability":"","data":{"blocks":[{"data":{},"depth":0,"entityRanges":[],"inlineStyleRanges":[],"key":"8k7ko","text":"During this step, it helps to secure at least two points of the membrane with a clean, gloved finger to prevent the PDMS from lifting off the first PMMA layer during cleaning.","type":"unstyled"}],"entityMap":{}}}}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"15leo","text":"Reinsert the taper pins into the bottom PMMA /PDMS","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"33dsg","text":"Inspect clean the top layer of PMMA using compressed air and MagicTape","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"79i6c","text":"Lower the top layer, feature side down, over the taper pins onto the lower PMMA layer and PDMS.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"cdpdu","text":"When the materials are close, press firmly from the center outwards to adhere all layers together.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"5tiu9","text":"Remove the taper pins","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"eq9b1","text":"Inspect the device to ensure features are aligned and there are no large air pockets. Small air pockets will smooth and disappear with annealing, wrinkles in the PDMS membrane will not.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"5a3d5","text":"Clean the outside of the device with compressed air and MagicTape","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"17skh","text":" ","type":"atomic","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[{"key":0,"offset":0,"length":1}],"data":{}},{"key":"ad8sn","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{"0":{"type":"notes","mutability":"","data":{"blocks":[{"data":{},"depth":0,"entityRanges":[],"inlineStyleRanges":[],"key":"8f5eq","text":"This step is mostly cosmetic. Dust or residue on the outside of the device may leave an imprint during the annealing process.","type":"unstyled"}],"entityMap":{}}}}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"3ash9","text":"Prepare two more pieces of PET/PDMS/PET \"bumper\" slightly larger than the size of the device (at least 30mm extra length and width)","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"c88k6","text":" ","type":"atomic","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[{"key":0,"offset":0,"length":1}],"data":{}},{"key":"8i48s","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{"0":{"type":"notes","mutability":"","data":{"blocks":[{"data":{},"depth":0,"entityRanges":[],"inlineStyleRanges":[],"key":"74ovb","text":"These pieces will be placed on the outside of the chip to help evenly distribute the pressure during compression. They will be removed after annealing.","type":"unstyled"}],"entityMap":{}}}}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"6ft14","text":"Crease one corner and peel away one layer of the PET from one of the bumpers","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"41sb2","text":" ","type":"atomic","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[{"key":0,"offset":0,"length":1}],"data":{}},{"key":"arvng","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{"0":{"type":"notes","mutability":"","data":{"blocks":[{"data":{},"depth":0,"entityRanges":[],"inlineStyleRanges":[],"key":"1pnpa","text":"Peel the PET away parallel again to create a sharp angle and facilitate the release of the two materials without wrinkles","type":"unstyled"}],"entityMap":{}}}}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"8gbk5","text":"Place the completed chip onto the exposed PDMS","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"fg0rt","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"aqvkn","text":"Peel one layer off PET from the other PET/PDMS/PET bumper and repeat for the other side of the chip","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"ekpha","text":"Sandwich the entire chip and bumpers between glass slides, ensuring the that entire device is between both slides. Parts that are not covered will not be compressed.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"fl5bb","text":" ","type":"atomic","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[{"key":0,"offset":0,"length":1}],"data":{}},{"key":"f2vjg","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"bnsvp","text":" ","type":"atomic","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[{"key":1,"offset":0,"length":1}],"data":{}},{"key":"fmb4n","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"910f5","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{"0":{"type":"notes","mutability":"","data":{"blocks":[{"data":{},"depth":0,"entityRanges":[],"inlineStyleRanges":[],"key":"al3g2","text":"Other rigid materials, like aluminum plates or larger pieces of glass, may also be used to compress the device.","type":"unstyled"}],"entityMap":{}}},"1":{"type":"result","mutability":"","data":{"blocks":[{"data":[],"depth":0,"entityRanges":[],"inlineStyleRanges":[],"key":"di30u","text":"From top to bottom, the product should be: Glass, PET, PDMS, PMMA, PDMS, PMMA, PDMS, PET, Glass","type":"unstyled"}],"entityMap":{}}}}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"35lgo","text":"Clamp with binder clips on all four sides.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"cgale","text":"Trim away any excess PDMS/PET bumper material","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"pdh","text":" ","type":"atomic","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[{"key":0,"offset":0,"length":1}],"data":{}},{"key":"9rsrl","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{"0":{"type":"notes","mutability":"","data":{"blocks":[{"data":{},"depth":0,"entityRanges":[],"inlineStyleRanges":[],"key":"1phr2","text":"A few mm of material sticking out is fine","type":"unstyled"}],"entityMap":{}}}}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"7eone","text":"Transfer to an oven, setting the device vertically in the middle of the oven.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"ep77n","text":"Heat to 110ºC and maintain temperature for long enough to heat the entire device thoroughly.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"for9q","text":" ","type":"atomic","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[{"key":0,"offset":0,"length":1}],"data":{}},{"key":"f30pd","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"btg99","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{"0":{"type":"notes","mutability":"","data":{"blocks":[{"data":{},"depth":0,"entityRanges":[],"inlineStyleRanges":[],"key":"bkmfu","text":"Time will vary depending on the oven. {"blocks":[{"key":"1rl1u","text":"Set the oven to room temperature and allow to cool completely (preferably over night).","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
